<!-- A-G REQUIREMENTS -->
<section class="sec sec-black" id="ag">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head-row">
      <div><div class="sec-eyebrow">UC &amp; CSU Admission</div><h2 class="sec-title">A–G Course<br>Requirements</h2></div>
      <div class="sec-head-desc">To be eligible for any UC or CSU campus, you must complete 15 college-prep courses with a C or better. Planning starts in 9th grade.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="ag-grid">
      <div class="ag-item"><div class="ag-badge">A</div><div class="ag-sub">History &amp; Social Science</div><div class="ag-yrs">2 Years Required</div><div class="ag-detail">1 year U.S. History + 1 year World History, Culture, or Geography. 1 semester U.S. Government may substitute for half of U.S. History.</div></div>
      <div class="ag-item"><div class="ag-badge">B</div><div class="ag-sub">English</div><div class="ag-yrs">4 Years Required</div><div class="ag-detail">College-prep English composition and literature all four years. AP English Language and AP English Literature both satisfy this requirement.</div></div>
      <div class="ag-item"><div class="ag-badge">C</div><div class="ag-sub">Mathematics</div><div class="ag-yrs">3 Years Required · 4 Recommended</div><div class="ag-detail">Algebra I, Geometry, Algebra II required. Pre-Calculus or AP Calculus strongly recommended. Statistics may count as the 4th year math.</div></div>
      <div class="ag-item"><div class="ag-badge">D</div><div class="ag-sub">Laboratory Science</div><div class="ag-yrs">2 Years Required · 3 Recommended</div><div class="ag-detail">Two different lab science disciplines. Biology, Chemistry, Physics preferred. AP Sciences count. Verify Earth Science eligibility with your counselor.</div></div>
      <div class="ag-item"><div class="ag-badge">E</div><div class="ag-sub">Language Other Than English</div><div class="ag-yrs">2 Years Required · 3 Recommended</div><div class="ag-detail">Two years of the same language. Spanish, Mandarin, ASL, etc. Heritage speakers may test out. Bay Area schools offer 3+ year sequences.</div></div>
      <div class="ag-item"><div class="ag-badge">F</div><div class="ag-sub">Visual &amp; Performing Arts</div><div class="ag-yrs">1 Year Required</div><div class="ag-detail">Dance, Drama/Theater, Music, or Visual Arts from the UC/CSU approved list. AP Art History, AP Music Theory, and AP Studio Art all count.</div></div>
      <div class="ag-item"><div class="ag-badge">G</div><div class="ag-sub">College-Prep Elective</div><div class="ag-yrs">1 Year Required</div><div class="ag-detail">An additional year from any A–F category, or from approved electives: Computer Science, Psychology, Economics, Political Science, Journalism.</div></div>
      <div class="ag-item" style="background:rgba(255,224,0,.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,224,0,.15);">
        <div style="font-size:2.2rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">🏆</div>
        <div class="ag-sub">GPA Requirement</div><div class="ag-yrs">3.0+ UC · 2.0+ CSU (Weighted)</div>
        <div class="ag-detail">UC uses weighted GPA — each AP/Honors/IB course adds 1 bonus point (max 8 semesters). Aim for 3.5+ weighted to be competitive at selective UCs.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ag-note"><div class="ag-note-icon">💡</div><div class="ag-note-text">Bay Area Tip: OUSD, SFUSD, WCCUSD, and other Bay Area districts have Dual Enrollment partnerships with Laney, Merritt, Berkeley City College, CCSF, and De Anza. College courses in high school satisfy A-G requirements AND earn transferable UC/CSU credit — for FREE. Talk to your counselor today.</div></div>
  </div>
</section>

