<!-- GLOSSARY -->
<section class="sec sec-gray" id="glossary">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head-row">
      <div><div class="sec-eyebrow">Know the Language</div><h2 class="sec-title">College Access<br>Glossary</h2></div>
      <div class="sec-head-desc">Don't let terminology slow you down. Master these terms and navigate the entire college process like the Genius you are.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="gloss-search"><span>🔍</span><input type="text" id="gsearch" placeholder="Search terms (FAFSA, PIQ, Cal Grant, A-G, HBCU...)"></div>
    <div class="gloss-grid" id="gloss-grid">
      <div class="gi" data-t="a-g requirements courses"><div class="gi-term">A-G Requirements</div><div class="gi-def">The 15 college-prep courses required for UC and CSU admission eligibility. Must be completed with a C or better in each subject area.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="ap advanced placement college board exam credit"><div class="gi-term">AP (Advanced Placement)</div><div class="gi-def">College-level high school courses. A score of 3, 4, or 5 on the AP Exam can earn college credit at many universities. Also boosts your weighted GPA.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="cal grant california free money financial aid"><div class="gi-term">Cal Grant A &amp; B</div><div class="gi-def">California's primary need-based grant program. Cal Grant A covers tuition; Cal Grant B provides a living expense allowance. Free money — never repaid. Apply via FAFSA by March 2.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="csu california state university sfsu san jose east bay"><div class="gi-term">CSU</div><div class="gi-def">California State University — a 23-campus teaching-focused system including SF State, San Jose State, Cal State East Bay, Cal Poly SLO, and Cal State Long Beach.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="uc university california berkeley ucla davis san diego"><div class="gi-term">UC (University of California)</div><div class="gi-def">California's research university system with 10 campuses: Berkeley, UCLA, San Diego, Davis, Santa Barbara, Irvine, Santa Cruz, Riverside, Merced, and SF (medical).</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="dual enrollment community college free credit high school"><div class="gi-term">Dual Enrollment</div><div class="gi-def">Taking community college courses while still in high school — for FREE. Credits satisfy A-G requirements AND transfer to UC/CSU. Bay Area: Laney, Merritt, CCSF, De Anza.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="eop educational opportunity program first gen low income"><div class="gi-term">EOP</div><div class="gi-def">Educational Opportunity Program — provides additional admissions consideration and campus support for first-generation and low-income students at UC and CSU campuses.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="fafsa federal student aid pell grant october deadline"><div class="gi-term">FAFSA</div><div class="gi-def">Free Application for Federal Student Aid. Opens October 1. Determines eligibility for Pell Grants, subsidized loans, and work-study. California's priority deadline is March 2.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="ca dream act california undocumented ab540 financial aid"><div class="gi-term">CA Dream Act</div><div class="gi-def">Alternative to FAFSA for AB 540-eligible and undocumented students. Provides access to the same California state aid programs. Apply at dream.csac.ca.gov.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="gpa grade point average weighted honors ap bonus"><div class="gi-term">GPA (Weighted)</div><div class="gi-def">Your academic score on a 4.0 scale. UC calculates a weighted GPA adding 1 bonus point for AP/IB/Honors courses (max 8 semesters). You need 3.0+ for UC eligibility.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="piq personal insight questions uc essays prompts 350 words"><div class="gi-term">PIQ (Personal Insight Questions)</div><div class="gi-def">UC's version of college essays. Choose 4 of 8 prompts, 350 words each. Your chance to share your story, identity, and perspective. Make it authentic and specific to you.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="common app application private college personal statement 650"><div class="gi-term">Common App</div><div class="gi-def">A single application platform used by 1,000+ colleges — primarily private and out-of-state schools. Includes a 650-word personal statement. UCs and most CSUs do NOT use Common App.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="mcs middle class scholarship california tuition uc csu income"><div class="gi-term">Middle Class Scholarship (MCS)</div><div class="gi-def">A California grant for families earning $0–$217k/year attending UC or CSU. Covers a percentage of tuition based on income. Apply via FAFSA or CA Dream Act by March 2.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="blue gold uc free tuition family income 80k promise"><div class="gi-term">UC Blue &amp; Gold Opportunity Plan</div><div class="gi-def">UC program guaranteeing families earning under $80k/year pay $0 in UC tuition and fees. Combined with Cal Grant, attending UC is often completely free for low-income students.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="tag transfer admission guarantee community college uc"><div class="gi-term">TAG (Transfer Admission Guarantee)</div><div class="gi-def">6 UC campuses guarantee admission to community college students who meet GPA and course requirements. An excellent pathway if direct UC admission is competitive for you.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="sat act test optional standardized admissions scores merit aid"><div class="gi-term">SAT / ACT</div><div class="gi-def">Standardized college admissions tests. UC and CSU are test-free for admissions. Many private colleges remain test-optional. Strong scores still help with merit scholarships.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="psat nmsqt national merit scholarship preliminary practice"><div class="gi-term">PSAT / NMSQT</div><div class="gi-def">Preliminary SAT taken in 10th and 11th grade. High scores can qualify for National Merit Scholarship recognition and the College Board National Recognition Programs.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="hbcu historically black colleges universities howard spelman morehouse"><div class="gi-term">HBCU</div><div class="gi-def">Historically Black Colleges &amp; Universities — 107 institutions including Howard, Spelman, Morehouse, Hampton, and FAMU. Strong Black community, mentorship, and scholarships.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="internship work experience professional career job shadow"><div class="gi-term">Internship</div><div class="gi-def">Professional work experience in a field of interest. Critical for college applications and career readiness. Many Bay Area companies offer high school internship programs.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="major minor undecided college field of study career"><div class="gi-term">Major / Minor</div><div class="gi-def">Your primary field of study (major) and optional secondary area (minor). You don't need to decide before applying — most colleges allow you to enter as undecided.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="postsecondary after high school university trade school bootcamp apprenticeship"><div class="gi-term">Postsecondary Education</div><div class="gi-def">Any education after high school: 4-year university, community college, trade school, coding bootcamp, military service, or apprenticeship. All are valid — choose based on YOUR goals.</div></div>
      <div class="gi" data-t="css profile private college financial aid additional application assets"><div class="gi-term">CSS Profile</div><div class="gi-def">A financial aid application required by many private colleges in addition to FAFSA. More detailed — includes home equity and business assets. Apply at cssprofile.collegeboard.org.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

