<!-- BREAKDOWN -->
<div class="sg-section">
  <div class="sg-section-eyebrow">Break it down</div>
  <div class="sg-section-title">What Each Letter Actually Means</div>
  <div class="sg-breakdown-grid">
    <div class="sg-bd-card">
      <div class="sg-bd-left"><div class="sg-bd-char">S</div><div class="sg-bd-word">Specific</div></div>
      <div class="sg-bd-right">
        <div class="sg-bd-q">What exactly do you want to accomplish?</div>
        <div class="sg-bd-desc">Vague goals give you nowhere to start. A specific goal names the what, who, and where. "Get better at coding" is a wish. "Complete two coding assignments using resources from office hours" is a goal.</div>
        <span class="sg-bd-tip">→ Ask: What exactly? Who's involved? Where?</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-bd-card">
      <div class="sg-bd-left"><div class="sg-bd-char">M</div><div class="sg-bd-word">Measurable</div></div>
      <div class="sg-bd-right">
        <div class="sg-bd-q">How will you know when you've hit it?</div>
        <div class="sg-bd-desc">If you can't measure it, you can't track it — and you'll never know when you've won. Add a number, frequency, or milestone. "Save money" → "save $200 by September, $25/week."</div>
        <span class="sg-bd-tip">→ Ask: How much? How many? How will I know?</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-bd-card">
      <div class="sg-bd-left"><div class="sg-bd-char">A</div><div class="sg-bd-word">Actionable</div></div>
      <div class="sg-bd-right">
        <div class="sg-bd-q">What steps will you take to get there?</div>
        <div class="sg-bd-desc">A goal needs verbs — things you can actually do. "Stop procrastinating" tells you nothing. "Write my essay by Monday and review it with my mentor" gives you two concrete steps to start today.</div>
        <span class="sg-bd-tip">→ Ask: What will I do — today, this week?</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-bd-card">
      <div class="sg-bd-left"><div class="sg-bd-char">R</div><div class="sg-bd-word">Realistic</div></div>
      <div class="sg-bd-right">
        <div class="sg-bd-q">Is this something you can actually pull off?</div>
        <div class="sg-bd-desc">Dream big, plan real. A realistic goal pushes you without breaking you. It's not about lowering your ambition — it's about setting a goal you can actually achieve given your schedule and energy.</div>
        <span class="sg-bd-tip">→ Ask: Do I have the time, skills, and resources?</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sg-bd-card">
      <div class="sg-bd-left"><div class="sg-bd-char">T</div><div class="sg-bd-word">Timebound</div></div>
      <div class="sg-bd-right">
        <div class="sg-bd-q">What's your deadline?</div>
        <div class="sg-bd-desc">Without a deadline, a goal is just a wish. A timebound goal creates forward pressure: "by Friday," "by end of month," "by graduation." Deadlines aren't traps — they're the structure that makes goals real.</div>
        <span class="sg-bd-tip">→ Ask: By when — exactly?</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

