    <div class="tip-card c-green">
      <div class="tip-icon-wrap">🗓️</div>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <div class="tip-num-badge">TIP 01</div>
        <div class="tip-title">Do a weekly time inventory</div>
        <p class="tip-desc">Before you can manage your time, you have to see where it's going. Every Sunday, spend 5 minutes writing out everything you're responsible for that week — school, HGP, sports, work, family. You can't protect time you don't see.</p>
        <span class="tip-action">→ Try it Sunday night</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-card c-blue">
      <div class="tip-icon-wrap">📱</div>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <div class="tip-num-badge">TIP 02</div>
        <div class="tip-title">Use Google Calendar — set recurring events</div>
        <p class="tip-desc">Download Google Calendar on your phone. Add your HGP programming, office hours, school schedule, and sports as recurring events. Turn on reminders 30 minutes early. When it's in your calendar, your phone becomes your accountability partner.</p>
        <span class="tip-action">→ Set it up today</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-card c-purple">
      <div class="tip-icon-wrap">🧱</div>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <div class="tip-num-badge">TIP 03</div>
        <div class="tip-title">Block your time — be specific</div>
        <p class="tip-desc">Don't schedule "study time" — schedule "Math chapter 4 review" or "write paragraph 2 of my English essay." Vague blocks get skipped. Specific blocks get done. Treat each block like a real appointment you can't cancel on yourself.</p>
        <span class="tip-action">→ Get specific, not general</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-card c-red">
      <div class="tip-icon-wrap">🔥</div>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <div class="tip-num-badge">TIP 04</div>
        <div class="tip-title">Identify your distractions — and plan for them</div>
        <p class="tip-desc">What gets in the way? Your phone? Your brothers? Feeling hungry? Whatever your pattern is, name it. Then build a workaround: put your phone in another room, eat before study blocks, let your people know when you're locked in. Discipline is just preparation.</p>
        <span class="tip-action">→ Name your #1 distraction</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-card c-teal">
      <div class="tip-icon-wrap">⚖️</div>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <div class="tip-num-badge">TIP 05</div>
        <div class="tip-title">Prioritize rest and self-care — it's not optional</div>
        <p class="tip-desc">Sleep is not something you give up to get more done. Teens need 8–9 hours. Your brain consolidates memory while you sleep — meaning skipping sleep actually hurts your grades. Block downtime just like you block study time. Rest is productive.</p>
        <span class="tip-action">→ Protect your sleep block</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-card c-gold">
      <div class="tip-icon-wrap">🔁</div>
      <div class="tip-body">
        <div class="tip-num-badge">TIP 06</div>
        <div class="tip-title">Review, adjust, and show your educator</div>
        <p class="tip-desc">Every week, check in on your planner. Did you stick to it? Where did things fall apart? What needs to shift next week? Show your planner to your educator to get checked off — they're there to help you refine it, not judge it. Accountability makes plans real.</p>
        <span class="tip-action">→ Review every Sunday</span>
      </div>
    </div>

